Parameter.Name: H+ Energy-Pitch Angle Distribution
Parameter.Set: Time series defined by using: Epoch
Parameter.Caveats: 64 solid angle bins are sorted into 16 pitch angles. Distribution is transformed into the plasma frame using the O+ convection velocity.

Parameter.Set: Time series defined by using: Epoch

Parameter.Set: Time series defined by using: Epoch
Parameter.Description: H+ omnidirectional energy flux vs energy in Plasma Frame
Parameter.Caveats: H+ distribution integrated over pitch angle to get omni-directional flux

Parameter.Name: Proton_Flag
Parameter.Set: Time series defined by using: Epoch
Parameter.Description: Proton Flag. Non-zero values indicate that incomplete data was used
Parameter.Caveats: This flag indicates that because of telemetry problems, there was no data for some angular bins. However, a full pitch angle distribution could be constructed. Data with nonzero flag should be used with caution.

Parameter.Name: Oxygen_Flag
Parameter.Set: Time series defined by using: Epoch
Parameter.Description: Oxygen Flag. Non-zero values indicate that incomplete data was used
Parameter.Caveats: This flag indicates that because of telemetry problems, there was no data for some angular bins. However, a full pitch angle distribution could be constructed. Data with nonzero flag should be used with caution.

Parameter.Name: Helium_Flag
Parameter.Set: Time series defined by using: Epoch_Helium
Parameter.Description: Helium Flag. Non-zero values indicate that incomplete data was used
Parameter.Caveats: This flag indicates that because of telemetry problems, there was no data for some angular bins. However, a full pitch angle distribution could be constructed. Data with nonzero flag should be used with caution.

Parameter.Name: Pitch_Angle
Parameter.Caveats: Pitch angle from 0 to 360 degrees, compatible with the iESA definition.

Parameter.Name: Loss_Cone_angle
Parameter.Set: Time series defined by using: Epoch
Parameter.Description: Loss Cone Angle calculating using a dipole model and 100 km mirror altitude
Parameter.Caveats: calculated from dipole magnetic field model and mirror altitude of 100 km

Parameter.Name: B_vec

Parameter.Name: H+ and O+ Deadtime flag
Parameter.Set: Time series defined by using: Epoch
Parameter.Description: H+ and O+ Deadtime flag. For each energy, indicates which deadtime algorithm was used.
Parameter.Caveats: Dead time flag. 0: rate<2e5 cts/s, Standard deadtime correction used,. 1: rate>2e5 cts/s. Use iESA to correct data.

Parameter.Name: He+ Deadtime flag
Parameter.Set: Time series defined by using: Epoch_Helium
Parameter.Description: He+ Deadtime flag. For each energy, indicates which deadtime algorithm was used.
Parameter.Caveats: Dead time flag. 0: rate<2e5 cts/s, Standard deadtime correction used,. 1: rate>2e5 cts/s. Use iESA to correct data.

Parameter.Name: Spacecraft Potential Flag
Parameter.Set: Time series defined by using: Epoch
Parameter.Caveats: 0: Data is corrected for spacecraft potential (until 2000-01-01/12:00:00), 1: No potential correction (2000-01-01/12:00:00-2003-01-01/12:00:00, 2: Data is corrected for charging of TEAMS front aperture (after 2003-01-01/12:00:0)

Parameter.Name: Spacecraft High Potential Warning
